        p.question 4. What if I don’t like the teacher you sent to our home?
        p
          | A. In that case we will send another teacher. You have the right to accept or reject any teacher. You should select the teacher only when you are completely satisfied.
        p.question 5. So does that mean I can meet any number of teacher?
        p
          | A. We will give you two free meetings. After the first meeting, our counsellor will get in touch with to note down your problems and specific requirements. This is because, each meeting involves travel and time commitment from the tutor.
        p.question 6. If I start classes with a tutor. Do I need to stick to the same tutor?
        p
          | A. No you can request tutor replacement at any point of time. You can talk to our counsellor and explain him/her the problems. Tutor replacement will take 2-3 days depending on the availability in your area.
        p.question 7. Is it safe to trust a stranger with our child?
        p
          | A. We advise students to take the classes in presence of parent/guardians.  We do not guarantee any safety.
        p.question 8. How do you ensure high quality tutors?
        p
          | A. We do quality check on all of our tutors. Though in some case your requirement may be different so you may not find a tutor suitable. In that scenario, we will provide you another tutor.
